race.comment: WITHIN THE LAW (14) was able to be ridden closer last start in the Flight after drawing a good gate and battled on well for second behind the dominant filly of her generation. More than capable of handling the boys, but another wide draw makes it trickier. MASTER OF THE AIR (4) thrashed a maiden field first-up then had to dig deep to just prevail last time in a Class 1 over 1400m at Kembla. By Dundeel so 1800m holds no fears. Heading the right way and can win again. The immaculately bred FEDERALIST (17) is yet to place in five starts but gave a glimmer of hope last Saturday in the Dulcify when he savaged the line to get up for fourth. Gets an extra furlong today on a quick back-up which is a good sign. Live chance. CHAMPAGNE HERO (8) bolted in at Newcastle recently and is still improving. In the right barn so don't take him lightly. Storm Boy's half-brother SHANGRI LA BOY (7) impressed last time at just his second race start. Should enjoy getting over more ground now.
